title.narrative: Programa de Desarrollo Juvenil - Fase I

description.narrative: Facilitar la transición de jóvenes en situación de riesgo al mundo de trabajo por capacitación, entrenamiento laboral, diseminación de información y servicios de intermediación laboral. Se financian actividades en las siguientes áreas estratégicas: (i) mejoramiento de los programas de capacitación ofrecidos por el Servicio Nacional de Juventud; (ii) promoción de centros de información para jóvenes; y (iii) fortalecimiento institucional del SNJ y del Centro Nacional para Desarrollo Juvenil, incluida la asistencia técnica para apoyar gobernabilidad y articulación entre varios sectores.

To facilitate the transition of unattached youth to adulthood and the world of work through training, on-the-job experience, information dissemination and labor intermediation services. Activities will be financed in three mutually supporting strategic areas: (i) enhancement of youth training and life skills offered by the National Youth Service (NYS); (ii) promotion of youth information centers building upon ongoing efforts in this area; and (iii) institutional strengthening to NYS and the National Center for Youth Development (NCYD), including technical assistance, to support governance and articulation between various sectors.

activity-description.narrative: This household survey captured data on youth and their perspectives on key issues like employment, empowerment and participation. It was part of a comprehensive process (including a Situation Analysis, Electronic Youth Programmatic Inventory and Gap Analysis) which will lead to updating of the National Youth Policy and improved legislation and programmes to assist youth in moving successfully into adulthood and employment.

This user-friendly website gives youth access to information on government programs and a job registration site and labour market information. The Website gives timely feedback on use of the site, participation in programs, and job search and job placement information. It also provides updates to youth stakeholders on ongoing revisions to the national Youth Policy.
